title: Ole Miss' Nkemdiche leaves game, has possible head injury
text:
Ole Miss' Nkemdiche leaves game, has possible head injury after offensive play THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   1:36 pmLast   1:36 pm   
Organizations: 
Mississippi (695) 

MEMPHIS, Tennessee â€” Mississippi's Robert Nkemdiche left Saturday's game against Memphis in the second quarter because of a possible head injury. 
Ole Miss said Nkemdiche's return was questionable. 
The 6-foot-5, 296-pound Nkemdiche, who usually plays defensive tackle, was injured while running the ball in a short-yardage situation. He's been used several times on offense this season and scored three touchdowns. 
AP college football website: collegefootball.ap.org
